  "updated_summary": "The segment opens with the 'Merrie Melodies' and 'The Wabbit who Came to Supper' title cards, followed by credits, all accompanied by orchestral music. In a dense forest, Bugs Bunny, panting and sweating, is pursued by a hunter with a rifle and then by four hounds. After exclaiming \"Trapped!\", Bugs confronts the dogs with a carrot, remarking, \"Oh boy, they flopped the wabbit!\". The hunter, informed by a telegram delivered by a mailman on a red scooter that he will inherit three million dollars but only if he harms no animals, sarcastically dismisses Bugs. The hunter storms to his pink house, labeled 'ELMER FUDD'. Inside, he confronts Bugs, who is wrapped in a towel behind a shower curtain in the bathroom. Bugs then comically grooms himself with a hairdryer, using 'Sissy Scent! by Tuna'. In the living room, the hunter pleads with Bugs not to call 'Uncle Woo-wee', promising not to harm him. Bugs agrees, then asks for food. The hunter, muttering \"I'll fix this guy\", storms out and slams the white door. Bugs taunts him, then feigns illness on the porch, claiming he'll get pneumonia and die. He whispers about an Academy Award before his act, then successfully opens the door. The hunter rushes out, sees Bugs seemingly unconscious, and laments, \"We million dollars all shot to pieces!\", sitting on Bugs in defeat."
