  "updated_summary": "Initially reclining on his back and reading 'VICTORY THRU HARE POWER' with a carrot, Bugs Bunny chuckles at the mention of Gremlins as a menace to pilots, dismissing them as a fairy tale. A dramatic orchestral sting and metallic clangs transition the scene to a desert landscape where Bugs sits atop a bomb. A small Gremlin Bird, dragging a massive wooden mallet with audible thumps and clangs, approaches. Bugs, munching his carrot, watches with a smug expression as the bird struggles. After a bomb dropping sound and Bugs' calm instruction to the bomb, the Gremlin Bird determinedly drags the mallet towards him. Bugs, feigning surprise, takes the mallet, mimics a boxer, and then drops it to perform comical dance moves while singing a taunting tune. He grins at the camera as the confused Gremlin Bird watches. The scene shifts again with Bugs atop the bomb, speculating if a sound was a Gremlin. The Gremlin Bird, exclaiming \"It ain't Bendoville key!\", attempts to strike the bomb with the mallet, producing a metallic clang. Bugs, unfazed, grabs the mallet, swings it wildly with whooshing sounds, performs dance moves, and ends with a loud \"THWACK!\" and \"BOING!\". He then asks an unseen \"George\" which way the Gremlin went, sarcastically thanking the bird for its direction. A whirring sound builds to a \"WHOOSH!\" and \"BOING!\" as the Gremlin Bird leaps onto Bugs' head, pulling at his ears. The bird taunts Bugs, who finally smirks triumphantly and responds with \"Uh-huh.\""
